      <p style="margin:0; font-size:var(--font-size-sm); color:var(--text-dark); line-height:1.6;">
        <strong>Calendar:</strong> 11th lunar day of the bright fortnight (Shukla Paksha) in Jyeshtha month (May/June)<br>
        <strong>Alternative Names:</strong> Nirjala Ekadasi, Bhimaseni Ekadasi, Pandava Dvadashi<br>
        <strong>Significance:</strong> The most powerful and austere Ekadasi. Fasting completely from water on this day yields the merit of all 24 Ekadasis in a year.<br>
        <strong>Rules:</strong> Strict fast from food and water (no water starting from sunrise on Ekadasi to sunrise on Dvadashi). Only achamana water (amount of a mustard seed) is permitted for purification.<br>
        <strong>Observance:</strong> Held on the scheduled event date. Please check the <a href="<?php echo BASE_URL; ?>festivals/vaishnava-calendar" style="color:var(--primary); font-weight:600; text-decoration:underline;">Vaishnava Calendar</a> for the exact day this year.
